SECURELY WIPE A MECHANICAL HARD DRIVE ON WINDOWS (DISKPART)
===========================================================

This guide shows how to completely erase a mechanical hard drive using only built‑in Windows tools.
This process destroys all data on the selected disk. Double‑check the disk number before running any commands.

-----------------------------------------------------------
1. OPEN COMMAND PROMPT AS ADMINISTRATOR
-----------------------------------------------------------
1. Click Start
2. Type: cmd
3. Right‑click "Command Prompt"
4. Select "Run as administrator"

-----------------------------------------------------------
2. START DISKPART
-----------------------------------------------------------
Type the following and press Enter:

diskpart

You should now see:
DISKPART>

-----------------------------------------------------------
3. LIST ALL DISKS
-----------------------------------------------------------
Type:

list disk

You will see something like:

Disk 0    476 GB
Disk 1    931 GB

Disk 0 is usually your Windows drive.
Other disks (Disk 1, Disk 2, etc.) are the ones you may want to wipe.

-----------------------------------------------------------
4. IDENTIFY THE CORRECT DISK
-----------------------------------------------------------
Look at the size of the disk you want to erase.
Make sure you know EXACTLY which disk number is correct.

-----------------------------------------------------------
5. SELECT THE TARGET DISK
-----------------------------------------------------------
Replace X with the correct disk number:

select disk X

Example:

select disk 1

DiskPart will confirm:
"Disk 1 is now the selected disk."

-----------------------------------------------------------
6. SECURELY WIPE THE DISK (THIS ERASES EVERYTHING)
-----------------------------------------------------------
Type:

clean all

This command writes zeros to every sector on the disk.
It can take hours on large mechanical drives.
Do not close the window or turn off the PC while it runs.

When finished, the disk will be completely blank.

-----------------------------------------------------------
7. OPTIONAL: CREATE A NEW PARTITION IF YOU WANT TO REUSE THE DRIVE
-----------------------------------------------------------
Type the following commands one at a time:

create partition primary
format fs=ntfs quick
assign
exit

The drive is now clean, empty, and ready to use again.

-----------------------------------------------------------
8. SUMMARY OF COMMANDS
-----------------------------------------------------------
diskpart
list disk
select disk X
clean all
create partition primary   (optional)
format fs=ntfs quick       (optional)
assign                     (optional)
exit

-----------------------------------------------------------
NOTES
-----------------------------------------------------------
- "clean all" is a secure wipe for mechanical hard drives.
- This method protects privacy and prevents data recovery.
- Be absolutely sure you select the correct disk number.
